"script": "Spin the dial on a combination lock, and three numbers magically pop it open. But there's no computer inside, just stacked metal discs. You see, behind the dial sit three wheels, each with a tiny notch cut into its edge. As you turn to the first number, you catch and line up one wheel's notch. Then the second number aligns the next, and the third aligns the last. Once all three notches face the same way, they form a perfect slot. And the latch drops straight in, springing the shackle open in your hand.",
